GOVERNMENT ORDER NO. CHANGE-2025 / P.S. 152 / E-3
Madam Kama Marg, Martyr Rajguru Chowk,
Reference: - The Maharashtra Regulation of Transfer of Government Employees and Prevention of Delays in the discharge of Government Duties Act, 2005

As per the provisions of Section 4 (4) w.e.f. 4 (5) of the Maharashtra Prevention of Delay in discharge of Government Duties and Regulation of Transfer of Government Employees Act, 2005, the officers of the following Tehsildar Cadre shall, for administrative reasons, be entitled to be produced in front of their name in Column No. The appointment to the post indicated in section 4 is being made with the approval of the competent authority in the interest of public service and for the convenience of the administrator.

2. The said order comes into immediate effect and the aforesaid officer issued the order in column no. Immediately join the position of the post mentioned in section 4. The concerned officer should immediately inform the Government by email / post at e3.revenue@maharashtra.gov.in of the date on which he / she appeared at the place of posting given to him / her. Orders regarding the appointment of Smt. Hansa Mohane, Tehsildar will be issued separately.

The officer concerned shall take care of joining the place of posting within the prescribed period as per the rules of the Maharashtra Civil Services (Period of assumption of office, Non-Service and Provisions during periods of suspension, dismissal and removal from service) Rules, 1981. Those concerned should note that their absence will count as "non-working days" (/ 7 €5 non) if they do not otherwise join the position of office.

4. Leave shall not be granted to the officer concerned for any reason except with the previous sanction of the Government. Also, as per Rule-30 (c) of the Maharashtra Civil Services (Leave) Rules, 1981, the original

The concerned shall note that in case of non-acceptance of appointment immediately under the said order or attempt to cancel the transfer under any kind of pressure, disciplinary action shall be taken against them on the ground that the act violates Rule 23 of the Maharashtra Civil Services (Conduct) Rules, 1979, treating it as misconduct.
